- "shone brightly in the market" refers to companies with high average and maximum closing prices; 
- "tech giants" refers to companies in the 'Technology' sector; 
- "milestone of $100" refers to an average closing price greater than $100.

- A "golden cross" is a chart pattern in which a short-term moving average (50-day) crosses above a long-term moving average (200-day), often seen as a bullish indicator; 
- The S&P 500 index is a stock market index that represents the market value of 500 large, publicly traded companies in the US; 
- The New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) is the world's largest stock exchange by total market capitalization of its listed companies.
